						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone in front of the temple of Hanumān.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1279.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the death by the rite of <hi rend="italic">samādhi,</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Chandi-gauḍi,</hi> the wife of <hi rend="italic">Sāvanta</hi> <hi rend="bold">Siriyama-gauḍa</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kaḍakoḷa.</hi> She was the lay disciple of <hi rend="bold">Padumasēna-Bhaṭṭāraka</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Mūla-saṁgha.</hi> The date of her death is cited as <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1201, Pramāthi, Bhādrapada śu. Shashṭhi, Monday,</hi> corresponding <hi rend="bold">to A.D. 1279, August 14, Monday, f.d.t. 12.</hi></p>						

						<p>A record of the grant of land made to a <hi rend="italic">basadi</hi> by <hi rend="bold">Hiriya-Boppa-gauḍa</hi> and others is added at the end.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
